<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-09-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="120" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 825.001/2.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Vice President of
                                    Chile</gloss> to President <persName type="to">Taft</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-09-08"><hi rend="italic">September 8,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Government and people of Chile will take grateful knowledge of the
                            telegram in which your excellency deigns to transmit the condolence of
                            the United States in our latest affliction.</p>
                        <p>Accept, excellency, my personal gratitude and the sentiments of my
                            highest and most distinguished consideration.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Emiliano
                            Figueroa.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>